FBIS3-14302 "drnes058_l_94007" FBIS-NES-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Kakh Activist Sentenced to 6 Months Imprisonment TA2403150094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 24 Mar 94 TA2403150094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] The Jerusalem Magistrate's Court has meted out a six month prison sentence to Tiran Pollak, a member of Kakh's Committee for Security on the Roads. Pollak was convicted of assault, disturbing a policeman, and rioting. Our police affairs correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports the judge acquiesced to Pollak's request to incarcerate him only after the Passover holiday.
